[SN]TITLE[SN]
Bury 0-1 Gillingham

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Gillingham strengthened their League One play-off push with victory at Bury.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Luke Norris got the only goal as he reacted quickest after Josh Wright's shot was blocked by a defender to calmly shoot home from eight yards out.
Ryan Jackson had a second-half shot saved by Bury's Chris Neal while Gills' Andrew Crofts also went close.
Bury fruitlessly pushed for an equaliser late on as Chris Hussey's free-kick went wide while Danny Rose forced a save from Stuart Nelson.
Gillingham, in fourth, now have a four-point cushion to seventh-placed Barnsley.
Bury manager David Flitcroft told BBC Radio Manchester:
